 object represents a one-dimensional shape located at a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"single geographical coordinate. Depending on how it is used, an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointAnnotation","isActive":true},{"text":" object is known as a point annotation or point shape. For","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"example, you could use a point shape to represent a city at low zoom levels, an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"address at high zoom levels, or the location of a long press gesture.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"title":"MapLibre","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolygon":{"title":"MLNMultiPolygon","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","abstract":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","isActive":true},{"text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"polygons that do not overlap. For example, you could use a multipolygon shape","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to represent the body of land that consists of an island surrounded by an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"atoll: the inner island would be one ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","isActive":true},{"text":" object, while the surrounding","type":"text"},{"text